1
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:37,000
I've said everything I needed to say.

2
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:40,080
About promoting the dragon boat race,

3
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:41,360
if you don't have any objections,

4
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:44,400
I'll proceed as I just outlined.

5
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:46,200
Thank you.

6
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:47,440
Anyway,

7
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,520
I share Secretary Peng's thoughts.

8
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:50,480
Don't overdo it.

9
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:51,720
After all, we represent the government.

10
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,960
I actually have a promotional idea.

11
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:56,000
If we can pull it off,

12
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:56,720
it'll be fantastic.

13
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:58,280
After the meal, I'll show you.

14
00:01:58,520 --> 00:01:59,120
Sounds good.

15
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,080
It actually can be paddled.

16
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:10,720
How should I put it...

17
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:12,400
I tried it myself,

18
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:13,680
and it works great.

19
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:15,960
Then let's

20
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:17,520
immediately

21
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,520
hurry to make a paper dragon boat

22
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:20,440
to enter the race.

23
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:24,720
It's still in the testing phase.

24
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:25,920
As a gimmick, it's fine.

25
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:27,160
But actually compete?

26
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:28,760
That doesn't matter.

27
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,400
If it performs well,

28
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:33,400
it'll be Lu Zhishen from *Water Margin*,

29
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,320
felling Zhen Guanxi with three punches,

30
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:36,760
making a name for itself in one battle.

31
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:37,800
If it performs badly,

32
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:40,840
it'll be Lin Daiyu from *Dream of the Red Chamber*,

33
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:42,560
stunningly beautiful,

34
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:44,040
melancholy and frail,

35
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:46,080
whose death evokes pity.

36
00:02:46,440 --> 00:02:47,800
Whatever the outcome,

37
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:50,560
it'll draw attention and gain fans.

38
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:52,800
Our promotional goal will be met.

39
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,280
Where's the

40
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:57,520
honest, kindhearted Teacher Liao I used to know?

41
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,160
All I see now is a

42
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:02,280
middle-aged influencer scheming for fame and gain.

43
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:03,240
Cut the nonsense.

44
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,040
Get on it.

45
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:05,440
Once it's made, it'll go viral.

46
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,160
Alright, let's do it.

47
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:08,640
To make your teacher even more famous,

48
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:10,000
hurry up and get to work.

49
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:11,600
Yes, sir.

50
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,640
Did something good happen?

51
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:35,560
I could hear you humming from far away.

52
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:37,920
Let me tell you.

53
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:40,240
Take a guess.

54
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:43,240
Where did Zhang Du go?

55
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:44,880
How would I know?

56
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,760
I just got a call from Old Lin.

57
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:48,960
He said Zhang Du

58
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:50,720
went to the drying yard.

59
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,080
Good, good, good.

60
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,480
As long as he's back.

61
00:03:58,080 --> 00:03:58,920
That's what matters.

62
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:00,400
Old Lin told me

63
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:03,080
he said this kid Zhang Du

64
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,640
isn't afraid of hardship or exhaustion.

65
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:08,360
All day he just buries himself in work.

66
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:10,240
Old Lin asked him,

67
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:11,440
"Zhang Du,

68
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,640
why did you come to the drying yard?"

69
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:15,040
Guess what Zhang Du said.

70
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:15,800
What did he say?

71
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:17,240
He said,

72
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:21,440
"I want to start from step one at the drying yard.

73
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:25,040
I want to be a true Xuan paper artisan."

74
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:26,160
He really said that?

75
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:29,320
Good.

76
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:31,400
What a good kid.

77
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:33,880
Good kid.

78
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:35,640
When Zhang Du said that,

79
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:38,080
deep in my heart,

80
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:42,320
I saw hope and something to look forward to.

81
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,800
Old Lin also told me

82
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:48,160
he said, from Zhang Du,

83
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:49,240
he could sense

84
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:52,760
this kid is just like a Qingtan tree.

85
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,480
A Qingtan tree.

86
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:01,360
"Unblessed in a past life,

87
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:05,200
born in Huizhou.

88
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:10,640
At thirteen or fourteen,

89
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:14,080
cast out into the world.

90
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:17,920
Bag on the shoulder,

91
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:21,600
the road stretching far.

92
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:25,520
Crossing hills and ranges,

93
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:29,520
sweat flowing endlessly.

94
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,480
Roaming north and south,

95
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:36,840
stars and moon as reward.

96
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:40,520
Are Mother and Father well?

97
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:43,760
Always on my mind.

98
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:48,000
Huizhou in my dreams,

99
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:52,080
the hills and streams unchanged."

100
00:05:57,760 --> 00:05:58,400
Zhang Du.

101
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,200
Come here, come here.

102
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,440
Put it down, put it down.

103
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:04,560
Put it down.

104
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,320
Take a break.

105
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:06,560
Alright.

106
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,440
Oh, you kid.

107
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:09,240
Not bad.

108
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,680
You aren't afraid of hard work,

109
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,200
and you don't rush either.

110
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:14,840
Listen to me.

111
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:17,000
This is like sharpening a blade.

112
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:18,880
Grind slowly.

113
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:22,240
As long as you don't grind the wrong side,

114
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:23,840
you're bound to succeed.

115
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:27,880
See?

116
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:30,440
Life is about enduring patiently.

117
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:33,440
When you endure like the Qingtan on the mountain,

118
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:36,040
success won't be far away.

119
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:37,680
Come, sit down.

120
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:39,760
The Qingtan.

121
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:40,680
Right.

122
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,040
Never restless.

123
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:45,760
Sunny days, the same.

124
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,240
Rainy days, the same.

125
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,320
Day or night, all the same.

126
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:51,680
Growing slowly,

127
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:53,520
until it becomes a tree.

128
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,880
Then it lets itself be cut down.

129
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:57,240
Whether its bark becomes paper,

130
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:59,160
or its core becomes a cane,

131
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:01,240
who dares say it's useless?

132
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:05,160
Even if you burn it as firewood,

133
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:06,240
it still gives off warmth.

134
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,400
It's bound to be useful.

135
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:11,160
I'll remember that, Master Lin.

136
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:13,760
Zhang Du,

137
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:16,320
in this life,

138
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:17,920
the road is long.

139
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:19,440
Walk it slowly.

140
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:21,360
As long as you walk steadily,

141
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:22,680
you'll do just fine.

142
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:50,920
Hold on a sec.

143
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:54,440
Let's puff up these bangs a little.

144
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:58,240
Take a look.

145
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,000
How is it?

146
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:04,920
It looks great.

147
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:08,280
Whenever my dad blow-dries my hair,

148
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:10,440
he makes me look like a lunatic.

149
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:11,920
Come here.

150
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:13,080
Take off your glasses.

151
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,800
Auntie will put some sunscreen on you.

152
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:17,480
That way your little face won't get tanned.

153
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,240
And over here too.

154
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:23,920
Okay.

155
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:24,440
Not bad.

156
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:25,560
A little on your hands too.

157
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:27,760
Go show your dad your hair.

158
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:28,560
Okay.

159
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,559
I... we...

160
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:35,880
A few people in our association,

161
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:37,320
like Fang Guangping and Ren Jiye,

162
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,080
you know them all, right?

163
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:40,200
We can bring them on board.

164
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:41,919
Our cultural creative business

165
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:43,320
is doing pretty well right now, isn't it?

166
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:44,720
Let them buy in as shareholders.

167
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:45,440
They'd jump at the chance.

168
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,680
We're running a business.

169
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:47,920
Business is business.

170
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,240
Don't turn it into a charity.

171
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:52,000
You can't put it that way.

172
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,240
What is this really about?

173
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:53,760
This is...

174
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:56,040
about showing our social responsibility as entrepreneurs.

175
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:57,120
Then how about this?

176
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:59,080
Give them your own shares.

177
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,040
I'd have no objection.

178
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,040
No way, no way.

179
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,760
You only gave me ten percent.

180
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:03,800
How am I supposed to split that?

181
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:04,320
I can't do it.

182
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,360
Split it however you want.

183
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:08,040
I'm going to buy Xiaoxing a drink.

184
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:08,840
I'll go with you.

185
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:09,680
No need.

186
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:12,200
Won't you reconsider?

187
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,480
Not listening, not listening, not listening.

188
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,000
Xiaoxing.

189
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,360
Just baked, fresh out.

190
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,240
How is it? Tasty?

191
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:21,200
Here.

192
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:21,680
What?

193
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,240
Things not going well?

194
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,440
Way to bring that up.

195
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:27,080
Have something warm to eat.

196
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,000
Grown-up matters,

197
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:30,200
kids shouldn't meddle.

198
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,000
Check, please.

199
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:33,560
We're not done with that yet.

200
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:34,360
You're already asking for the bill?

201
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:37,120
Your situation isn't gonna wrap up anytime soon.

202
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:38,520
Couldn't you tell?

203
00:09:38,520 --> 00:09:39,600
She's not into you.

204
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:40,560
What do you mean not into me?

205
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:41,520
What do you know?

206
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:42,800
She may not be into me,

207
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:44,400
but as long as I'm into her, that's enough, right?

208
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:45,320
How much?

209
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,560
Hi, forty-five yuan in total.

210
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:48,680
Sorry about this.

211
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:50,000
I forgot my phone.

212
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:50,840
Just wait a moment.

213
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,200
Sure.

214
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:51,880
I'll be right back.

215
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,920
Daddy paid to bring you along

216
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,200
so you'd help Daddy win over Auntie Xin Ran.

217
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,360
You can't just take a little knife behind my back

218
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,760
and keep stabbing me in the back.

219
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:03,160
You have to help me,

220
00:10:03,160 --> 00:10:04,880
right up until Auntie Xin Ran says yes.

221
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,600
You'd better explain yourself today.

222
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,160
What on earth are you doing with all that money?

223
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:11,200
None of your business.

224
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,240
You have to tell me.

225
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:12,760
Xiao Min.

226
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:15,200
Xin Ran.

227
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,120
You two really know how to scheme.

228
00:10:19,880 --> 00:10:21,520
Good thing I forgot my phone,

229
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:22,800
otherwise I'd never have known

230
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,040
you two have been using me as a bargaining chip.

231
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:24,800
Auntie Xin, Xin Ran.

232
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:26,360
You've got it wrong.

233
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:26,800
Auntie Xin.

234
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:27,520
It really is a misunderstanding.

235
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:28,520
We were just joking around.

236
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:29,760
Xin Ran, Xin Ran, Xin Ran.

237
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:30,360
You've really got it wrong.

238
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,000
Don't bother explaining.

239
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,920
Auntie Xin, Auntie Xin.

240
00:10:33,160 --> 00:10:35,120
Auntie Xin, Auntie Xin.

241
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:47,600
Careful now.

242
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:50,960
How is it, Teacher Liao?

243
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:53,760
The structure's solid.

244
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:55,480
The flexibility's good too.

245
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,400
I'm actually feeling confident now.

246
00:10:58,120 --> 00:10:58,960
This whole thing,

247
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:00,160
we owe it all to Uncle Lin.

248
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,360
If Uncle Lin didn't have such clout,

249
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:03,720
those craftsmen from Linjia Village

250
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,040
who make dragon boats

251
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:07,000
would never make anything for us.

252
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:11,840
Xuan Yan,

253
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:14,760
whether this takes off is up to you.

254
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:17,640
Don't make a fool of me out there.

255
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:19,480
Don't worry, Teacher Liao.

256
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:22,000
Phone's ringing.

257
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:26,480
Hello, what's up?

258
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:30,520
I'll be right back.

259
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:32,880
Yiran.

260
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:34,320
Come home with me.

261
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:37,000
No, what's going on?

262
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,000
No, what happened?

263
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:46,560
What's this about?

264
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:47,800
Explain yourself.

265
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:49,120
This paper,

266
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:50,320
we had it authenticated.

267
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:51,320
It's brand new.

268
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:53,880
You marked it up and sold it as aged paper.

269
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:56,160
Isn't that blatant fraud?

270
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:57,720
Isn't this preying on old folks?

271
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,480
Isn't it?

272
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,240
Exactly.

273
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:05,040
And you still won't admit it.

274
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:07,120
Your shop's label is right on it.

275
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:07,840
Right.

276
00:12:08,040 --> 00:12:08,920
Right, there's a label.

277
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:09,960
There's a label, there's a label.

278
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:10,840
Let me have a look.

279
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:11,280
There's a label.

280
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:17,520
Master craftsman,

281
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:18,960
please tell me,

282
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:21,400
what on earth is going on here?

283
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:23,320
Where did you buy this paper?

284
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,400
Who sold it to you?

285
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:26,000
Who says this is Xuan family paper?

286
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:28,000
She did.

287
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:29,240
She sold it to us.

288
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,760
It's her, it's her, it's her!

289
00:12:30,760 --> 00:12:32,640
She sold us new paper as aged paper.

290
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:33,520
Yiran's mom.

291
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:34,120
You.

292
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,480
Come here and explain this to everyone.

293
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,400
Wait, sis,

294
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:37,920
can we talk about this off to the side?

295
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:39,120
What's this all about?

296
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:39,720
Let's...

297
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:41,720
She's the one who sold it to us.

298
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:42,240
She's the seller.

299
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:43,240
No, no.

300
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:46,480
The thing is, these old gentlemen,

301
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:47,720
they don't really know much.

302
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:50,120
He can't tell aged paper from old paper.

303
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:51,480
I think regarding your appraisal,

304
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,320
you must have been fooled or scammed.

305
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:54,600
The appraisers are all professionals.

306
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:55,640
How could they get it wrong?

307
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:56,480
You're a liar.

308
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:57,520
Yiran's mom,

309
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,240
is this Xuan family paper?

310
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,000
Of course it's Xuan family paper.

311
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:03,880
I got it right here from you.

312
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:06,280
And I took it as aged paper at the time.

313
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:06,840
Hold on a second.

314
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:07,600
Aged paper?

315
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:10,760
You say you got this paper from the Xuan family.

316
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:12,960
The Xuan family members are all right here.

317
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:14,880
Point out who it was

318
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:17,120
that gave you this paper.

319
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,000
Right, right, right.

320
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:18,520
Speak clearly.

321
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:19,600
Tell us, tell us, who was it?

322
00:13:21,160 --> 00:13:23,160
It was... it was your wife who gave it to me.

323
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:24,960
Yiran's mom,

324
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,320
don't talk nonsense.

325
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:27,440
It was because you had no money

326
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,000
that sister Xiumei sold you paper on credit.

327
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:31,280
We never said we sold you aged paper.

328
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:31,960
No, no.

329
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:33,760
I... I don't really understand these things.

330
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:35,680
How would I know new paper from aged paper?

331
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:37,720
All I know is I got it from you.

332
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:39,160
And I took it as aged paper.

333
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:40,360
Let me tell you,

334
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:43,640
the Xuan family has made Xuan paper for ages.

335
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:45,240
And we sell Xuan paper too.

336
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:47,280
But we have a family rule:

337
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:49,960
whoever cheats,

338
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:51,880
gets their fingers chopped off.

339
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:53,000
That's right.

340
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:53,960
No, no, no.

341
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:54,720
No.

342
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,120
What does that have to do with me?

343
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:58,720
What do you mean I cheated?

344
00:13:58,720 --> 00:13:59,960
You gave me the aged paper.

345
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:00,480
So really,

346
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:02,120
this has nothing to do with me.

347
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:03,520
You're talking absolute nonsense.

348
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:05,160
You're stirring up trouble

349
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:06,880
and slandering the Xuan family.

350
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:08,240
Let me tell you,

351
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:09,560
don't spout nonsense.

352
00:14:09,560 --> 00:14:11,320
A thousand years of Xuan paper, a thousand years of Xuan family.

353
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:13,840
The Xuans value reputation more than life itself.

354
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:15,640
Thousand-year Xuan family, my foot!

355
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:17,680
I just thought your Xuan paper

356
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:19,680
was sitting in the warehouse with nowhere to sell.

357
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:20,920
I wanted to help you.

358
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:22,000
What did you think?

359
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,160
Thousand-year Xuan family?

360
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:25,000
Your paper isn't worth a penny.

361
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:25,480
Mom!

362
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:35,200
Call someone!

363
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,160
My head hurts.

364
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:12,640
I-I'm sorry, ma'am.

365
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:32,160
Xuan Yan.

366
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:36,520
I'm sorry.

367
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:41,600
Family of Xuan Yongnian?

368
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:43,120
Come with me for a moment.

369
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:44,240
Mom.

370
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:45,760
I'll go.

371
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:49,000
You... you go back first.

372
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,000
Auntie.

373
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:22,200
As for my mom...

374
00:16:25,280 --> 00:16:28,200
I'm... I'm sorry, Auntie.

375
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:36,520
Miss Lin.

376
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:54,160
Right.

377
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,600
I'm sorry, auntie.

378
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,520
I'm sorry.

379
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:05,319
I'm sorry, auntie.

380
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:22,400
Have some water.

381
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,120
I really never imagined

382
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:34,000
that my mom would do something like this.

383
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:43,400
Don't be sad.

384
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:47,400
Director Liao and I

385
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:49,880
have already settled the refund money

386
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:52,000
for the paper returned by the senior school.

387
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:53,600
It's all taken care of.

388
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:55,880
Wait,

389
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:57,000
where did the money come from?

390
00:17:57,880 --> 00:17:58,880
Director Liao's.

391
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:01,320
His private savings from over twenty years,

392
00:18:01,560 --> 00:18:03,240
he took it all out at once.

393
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,280
So don't be sad anymore.

394
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:12,920
I just transferred you ten thousand.

395
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:14,600
Tomorrow, go to the hospital

396
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:16,200
and settle the bill.

397
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,480
Just to show your good faith.

398
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:22,000
Uncle... Uncle Xuan,

399
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,800
I got him into that state.

400
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:26,720
He and Auntie Xu have been so good to me.

401
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:27,760
Tell me, how am I

402
00:18:29,560 --> 00:18:31,640
supposed to face them from now on?

403
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:44,800
Why are you crying so hard?

404
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,480
Eat your food while it's still hot.

405
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:49,680
Director Liao.

406
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:19,600
You've got us here.

407
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:34,080
Here, have some water.

408
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:39,080
Resigning over such a small matter?

409
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:43,600
Backing down when facing problems?

410
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:45,920
That's not the Lin Yiran I know.

411
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:48,760
Your reason for resigning isn't enough.

412
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:50,040
This Secretary won't approve it.

413
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:53,440
Secretary Peng, I...

414
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:55,400
Tell you what.

415
00:19:56,080 --> 00:19:57,600
I'll grant you two days off.

416
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:59,320
Get some rest and clear your head.

417
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:00,080
How's that?

418
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:05,240
What's the big deal?

419
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:07,360
Just face it and solve it.

420
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:09,000
It's really nothing.

421
00:20:09,560 --> 00:20:10,440
I believe...

422
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:13,800
you won't let me down, right?

423
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:21,600
Thank you, Secretary Peng.

424
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:23,520
Now that's the Lin Yiran I know.

425
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:24,440
Drink up.

426
00:20:55,160 --> 00:20:56,400
Mom, Dad.

427
00:20:57,040 --> 00:20:58,240
I brought the food.

428
00:20:58,600 --> 00:20:59,400
I'll leave it here.

429
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:00,760
Eat it while it's hot.

430
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:03,000
I've got things to do at Daya Studio.

431
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:04,920
I'll head back and come by later.

432
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:09,040
Bed 402.

433
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:10,800
Someone paid your bill again.

434
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:11,800
Tell her something.

435
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:12,960
His condition is stable now.

436
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:14,240
Don't pay so much anymore.

437
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:15,880
Okay, okay.

438
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:20,240
It was Miss Lin again, wasn't it?

439
00:21:21,080 --> 00:21:21,720
Yes.

440
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,000
Yes.

441
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:24,040
I'll get going now.

442
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:29,360
Chin up, chest out.

443
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:30,320
Look sharp.

444
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:33,240
Got it, Mom.

445
00:21:33,520 --> 00:21:34,520
Bye, Dad.

446
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:40,440
You have to talk to Xiao Lin.

447
00:21:41,320 --> 00:21:43,920
Don't let her pay the bills anymore.

448
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:46,240
I've told her so many times.

449
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:47,480
Told her not to pay.

450
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:48,760
I even called her.

451
00:21:48,760 --> 00:21:49,600
She wouldn't pick up.

452
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:51,520
She just replied on WeChat, saying:

453
00:21:51,520 --> 00:21:53,640
"Auntie, it's the least I can do."

454
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:54,600
"I'm sorry."

455
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:57,400
No way.

456
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:58,400
This isn't right.

457
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:03,560
You don't blame her, do you?

458
00:22:05,560 --> 00:22:07,120
Why would I blame her?

459
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:11,760
Her mom is her mom.

460
00:22:11,760 --> 00:22:12,720
She's her own person.

461
00:22:12,880 --> 00:22:14,080
They're separate people.

462
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:15,960
Even so,

463
00:22:16,520 --> 00:22:18,320
I wouldn't blame either of them.

464
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:19,760
On this matter,

465
00:22:21,080 --> 00:22:22,200
I know the difference.

466
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:27,800
That's what I've loved about you my whole life.

467
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,240
Your open-mindedness.

468
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:32,640
A chancellor's belly can scoop up paper.

469
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:35,840
It's "A chancellor's belly can hold a boat."

470
00:22:36,080 --> 00:22:38,240
Not "scoop up paper."

471
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:41,800
Sometimes I wonder,

472
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:42,720
you know,

473
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:45,240
if we ever became in-laws with her,

474
00:22:45,760 --> 00:22:48,160
how would you get along with that woman?

475
00:22:48,760 --> 00:22:51,240
If we get along, we visit more often.

476
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:53,800
And if we don't?

477
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:55,600
Then we meet less.

478
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:57,640
As for courtesies,

479
00:22:57,640 --> 00:22:59,280
we do whatever's proper.

480
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:00,200
Not rude,

481
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:01,960
not overdone.

482
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:03,440
Isn't that enough?

483
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:08,320
Tell me,

484
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:11,760
our son used to be so lively,

485
00:23:12,040 --> 00:23:13,400
such a cheerful person.

486
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:14,760
These past few days, because of this,

487
00:23:15,240 --> 00:23:16,000
well,

488
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:18,040
he doesn't seem too happy.

489
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:19,320
It's fine.

490
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:21,120
With your attitude now,

491
00:23:21,320 --> 00:23:22,760
he'll feel a lot more at ease.

492
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:54,600
Lin Yiran.

493
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:00,400
Lin Yiran!

494
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:26,840
Why aren't you answering your phone?

495
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:29,000
Mr. Xuan, you're here.

496
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:29,960
Jiajia.

497
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:31,240
Where's Lin Yiran?

498
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:34,000
She didn't tell you?

499
00:24:34,520 --> 00:24:35,280
No, she didn't say anything.

500
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:36,000
What's going on?

501
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:38,440
Director Lin is on leave.

502
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:39,320
On leave?

503
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:41,760
Do you know where she went?

504
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:44,400
That, I really don't know.

505
00:24:45,040 --> 00:24:46,040
Alright, thanks.

506
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:51,000
Where could she have gone?

507
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:49,800
It's okay.

508
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:51,400
It's all over now.

509
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:53,360
My dad woke up too.

510
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:55,640
Don't feel so bad anymore.

511
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:04,800
Let's break up.

512
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:08,640
I know.

513
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:11,280
You can't get over it right away.

514
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:13,120
You feel this whole thing

515
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:14,520
was all caused by you.

516
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:16,440
I get that you need some space,

517
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:18,600
but we don't have to break up.

518
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:23,520
I've thought it through.

519
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:27,680
Breaking up is the only

520
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:30,280
outcome that's good for both of us.

521
00:26:30,840 --> 00:26:31,680
Good, my ass.

522
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:34,320
You're wrong to think that way, Lin Yiran.

523
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:37,240
Do you think my parents

524
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:38,200
would blame you?

525
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:40,480
No, they totally understand you.

526
00:26:41,320 --> 00:26:42,320
How can you be so sure

527
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:43,800
that they really understand me?

528
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:47,320
Sometimes I don't even understand myself.

529
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:50,440
Because you've never been through

530
00:26:50,440 --> 00:26:51,520
a family of origin like mine.

531
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:52,400
So you don't get it.

532
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:55,240
You know what, Xuan Yan?

533
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:58,160
When I'm with you,

534
00:26:58,160 --> 00:26:59,680
I feel like I'm just a burden.

535
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:01,000
Haven't you noticed

536
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:02,040
that ever since we got together,

537
00:27:02,040 --> 00:27:03,600
your family's troubles never stop?

538
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:07,400
Let's just leave it at that.

539
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:08,520
No, why would you think that?

540
00:27:09,040 --> 00:27:09,800
Lin Yiran.

541
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,640
None of it is your fault.

542
00:27:14,560 --> 00:27:15,720
But she's my mom.

543
00:27:16,400 --> 00:27:17,520
I can't just ignore her.

544
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:19,520
No matter what I do,

545
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:20,640
I can't change the situation.

546
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:21,600
What do you want me to do?

547
00:27:22,320 --> 00:27:23,200
It's okay.

548
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:24,480
I can be there with you,

549
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:26,480
face your family of origin together.

550
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:29,760
Why do you have to carry everything alone?

551
00:27:29,760 --> 00:27:31,040
You're not some god.

552
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:33,800
Don't be so hard on yourself, okay?

553
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:35,520
Past misfortunes don't mean

554
00:27:35,520 --> 00:27:37,120
you'll be unhappy forever.

555
00:27:37,120 --> 00:27:37,880
Right?

556
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:39,800
You're way stronger than me.

557
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:41,120
And my parents,

558
00:27:41,200 --> 00:27:42,760
they really like you.

559
00:27:45,520 --> 00:27:46,440
Let's just leave it at that.

560
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:50,520
At least let me keep some dignity.

561
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:14,520
Look at this whole mess.

562
00:28:16,080 --> 00:28:17,720
If Master and Madam find out,

563
00:28:17,760 --> 00:28:19,040
they'll be so disappointed.

564
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:20,320
Especially my master.

565
00:28:20,320 --> 00:28:21,960
With his health the way it is,

566
00:28:22,320 --> 00:28:23,760
losing such a wonderful daughter-in-law,

567
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:25,080
he'd be devastated.

568
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:27,720
I didn't tell them the truth.

569
00:28:29,320 --> 00:28:30,440
I said she's been busy lately

570
00:28:31,320 --> 00:28:32,120
and can't come back.

571
00:28:35,520 --> 00:28:36,440
Let's just leave it at that for now.

572
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:38,560
The soup's ready.

573
00:28:38,560 --> 00:28:39,200
Let's eat.

574
00:28:39,520 --> 00:28:39,800
No, thanks.

575
00:28:40,320 --> 00:28:41,280
Xuan Yan, come eat.

576
00:28:42,520 --> 00:28:43,520
Come have some food, Xuan Yan.

577
00:28:52,360 --> 00:28:53,160
Xuan Yan.

578
00:28:54,080 --> 00:28:55,240
Don't worry too much.

579
00:28:55,240 --> 00:28:57,800
I'll go talk to Yiran again in a few days, okay?

580
00:28:58,440 --> 00:28:59,760
Let's just eat first, alright?

581
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:03,800
I'm fine.

582
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:04,800
I'm heading home.

583
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:05,560
I'm tired.

584
00:29:06,240 --> 00:29:06,840
Xuan Yan.

585
00:29:07,560 --> 00:29:08,240
I'm okay.

586
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:09,960
You still need to eat.

587
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:12,920
I'm not that hungry. I don't feel like it.

588
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:20,520
Mr. Xin.

589
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:21,480
The food's gone cold.

590
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:22,000
I'm sorry.

591
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:22,880
I won't be eating either.

592
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:24,400
Mr. Xin.

593
00:29:24,840 --> 00:29:25,440
Mr. Xin!

594
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:29,520
Yesterday, Xiaoxing's teacher

595
00:29:29,520 --> 00:29:30,760
called me to the school.

596
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:34,760
Xiaoxing's been in a really bad mood lately.

597
00:29:34,760 --> 00:29:36,160
She's been fighting with classmates a lot.

598
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:38,760
I gave her a harsh scolding,

599
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:41,000
and right in front of the teacher,

600
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:42,280
she got into a huge argument with me.

601
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:44,240
She flat-out refuses to let me attend tomorrow's parent meeting.

602
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:46,160
She said if I show up tomorrow,

603
00:29:47,760 --> 00:29:49,520
she'll never see me again for the rest of her life.

604
00:30:10,920 --> 00:30:11,240
You...

605
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:12,800
Last night,

606
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:15,680
I thought about it all night.

607
00:30:18,520 --> 00:30:19,800
The root of the problem is me.

608
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:24,120
Around the time Xiaoxing's mom passed away,

609
00:30:24,520 --> 00:30:26,240
our factory was under heavy financial pressure.

610
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:28,840
Nothing was going right.

611
00:30:29,080 --> 00:30:30,240
And my temper was bad.

612
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:32,320
It was during that time

613
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:34,000
that I failed my child.

614
00:30:34,840 --> 00:30:36,800
I lacked patient guidance and love.

615
00:30:38,280 --> 00:30:40,240
My parenting was harsh and crude.

616
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:41,520
I'd yell at her over nothing.

617
00:30:44,560 --> 00:30:45,760
Chairman Xiao,

618
00:30:46,840 --> 00:30:48,440
do you know what your biggest problem is?

619
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:49,040
Do you?

620
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:54,520
You don't know what Xiaoxing fears most.

621
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:01,040
Something she came to believe at five years old.

622
00:31:01,040 --> 00:31:03,240
That people who love her will leave.

623
00:31:03,600 --> 00:31:05,600
Xiaoxing has never been

624
00:31:05,600 --> 00:31:07,160
a problem child.

625
00:31:07,160 --> 00:31:07,760
On the contrary,

626
00:31:08,360 --> 00:31:11,720
she's a child carrying childhood trauma

627
00:31:11,720 --> 00:31:13,880
who's still trying hard to grow.

628
00:31:18,600 --> 00:31:20,520
I'm in no position to lecture you,

629
00:31:21,600 --> 00:31:24,240
but I want to remind you of one thing.

630
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:25,800
If you want to change all this,

631
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:27,040
the only way

632
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:28,200
is to change yourself first.

633
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:29,600
Watch your mouth,

634
00:31:29,600 --> 00:31:31,040
control your temper,

635
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:33,440
and through your actions,

636
00:31:34,600 --> 00:31:35,400
your love,

637
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:37,240
and your time,

638
00:31:40,600 --> 00:31:42,520
win back your child's trust.

639
00:31:50,080 --> 00:31:50,800
Teacher,

640
00:31:51,120 --> 00:31:52,080
this kid got beaten up,

641
00:31:52,080 --> 00:31:53,600
and their parents never showed up.

642
00:31:53,640 --> 00:31:54,960
You have to give me an explanation.

643
00:31:54,960 --> 00:31:56,080
Let's talk after the meeting.

644
00:31:56,520 --> 00:31:56,760
We'll discuss it later.

645
00:31:56,760 --> 00:31:56,960
Okay.

646
00:32:01,520 --> 00:32:02,240
Xiao Xiaoxing,

647
00:32:02,640 --> 00:32:03,920
why isn't your parent here yet?

648
00:32:06,520 --> 00:32:08,160
Is he skipping out again?

649
00:32:14,840 --> 00:32:15,920
Then we won't wait.

650
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:17,040
Let's get started now.

651
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:22,240
Sorry, everyone.

652
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:23,160
I'm late.

653
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:25,160
Hello, teacher.

654
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:27,000
I'm Xiao Xiaoxing's parent.

655
00:32:28,800 --> 00:32:29,800
Please, have a seat.

656
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:42,200
Alright, let's begin now

657
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:43,520
with today's parent-teacher meeting.

658
00:32:43,840 --> 00:32:45,680
This meeting has two parts.

659
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:47,280
The first part

660
00:32:47,280 --> 00:32:49,520
is a summary of the recent exam results.

661
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:50,800
The second part

662
00:32:50,800 --> 00:32:52,200
concerns the psychological development

663
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:53,160
of our eighth-grade students.

664
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:01,520
Master.

665
00:33:04,080 --> 00:33:05,120
Why are you out of bed?

666
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:08,720
I wanted to check

667
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:10,720
if the Qingtan bark's been soaked.

668
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:12,640
The bark's already soaking.

669
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:13,720
It's soaking?

670
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:14,720
Are you sure?

671
00:33:16,840 --> 00:33:17,600
Yes, yes, yes.

672
00:33:18,720 --> 00:33:20,200
I remember now, it's been soaked.

673
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:20,920
Yongnian.

674
00:33:21,280 --> 00:33:22,200
Didn't I tell you

675
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:24,200
to get more rest?

676
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:25,520
Why are you up again?

677
00:33:25,520 --> 00:33:26,840
Stay in bed a bit longer.

678
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:28,800
I'm not used to it.

679
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:30,400
Just lying around there,

680
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:32,760
with so many problems

681
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:35,080
that still need solving.

682
00:33:35,920 --> 00:33:37,440
You're a workhorse, that's what you are.

683
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:40,880
How are things at the mill now?

684
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:42,520
Same as when you left.

685
00:33:42,800 --> 00:33:43,880
Nothing's changed.

686
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:45,000
I just...

687
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:48,760
What is it?

688
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:52,800
All this paper we've made for months,

689
00:33:53,560 --> 00:33:55,440
we haven't even sold a fifth of it.

690
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:57,240
Xuan Yan cleared out

691
00:33:57,840 --> 00:33:59,640
most of the warehouse a while back.

692
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:00,920
But now

693
00:34:01,720 --> 00:34:03,000
it's almost full again.

694
00:34:03,560 --> 00:34:04,480
No rush.

695
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:06,200
We'll sell it gradually.

696
00:34:06,880 --> 00:34:10,400
The big mills like Xiao Min's and Ren Jiye's

697
00:34:10,880 --> 00:34:12,960
have all set up wallpaper production lines.

698
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:14,480
And they're making money.

699
00:34:14,679 --> 00:34:16,480
Our handmade wallpaper

700
00:34:16,679 --> 00:34:17,960
is just too expensive.

701
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:20,159
Enough.

702
00:34:20,719 --> 00:34:23,480
Forget about the wallpaper.

703
00:34:23,679 --> 00:34:24,440
As for us,

704
00:34:24,600 --> 00:34:26,120
we'll just stick to our roots

705
00:34:26,120 --> 00:34:28,280
and protect the family trade

706
00:34:29,199 --> 00:34:30,000
our ancestors passed down.

707
00:34:30,440 --> 00:34:32,159
Live one day, guard it one day.

708
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:34,239
As long as we don't go hungry, that's enough.

709
00:34:35,040 --> 00:34:36,480
I guess that's all we can do.

710
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:38,480
Lately we've been making

711
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:41,679
a lot of Extra-pure Bark Paper.

712
00:34:41,719 --> 00:34:43,040
Why don't you take a look

713
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:45,520
and see which type sells better?

714
00:34:45,719 --> 00:34:47,000
We could switch it up.

715
00:34:47,040 --> 00:34:48,239
Then what should we make?

716
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:50,960
Yongnian,

717
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:54,080
you used to handle all this without me asking.

718
00:34:55,239 --> 00:34:57,840
You'd make the calls clearly on your own.

719
00:34:57,840 --> 00:34:58,520
But now you...

720
00:34:59,920 --> 00:35:01,160
Tell you what, this matter,

721
00:35:01,920 --> 00:35:03,000
just tell Xiumei about it

722
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:04,320
and let her handle it.

723
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:10,480
These past few days,

724
00:35:10,480 --> 00:35:11,760
I've been lying in bed

725
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:13,040
thinking about a lot of things.

726
00:35:14,040 --> 00:35:15,000
But

727
00:35:16,040 --> 00:35:17,400
I just can't make up my mind.

728
00:35:17,920 --> 00:35:18,400
Let's do this.

729
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:19,360
Let's go over to your place,

730
00:35:20,040 --> 00:35:21,720
and the two of us can have a good talk.

731
00:35:23,240 --> 00:35:23,760
Come on.

732
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:30,280
Senior brother.

733
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:31,960
You go ahead.

734
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:33,560
Let's go.

735
00:35:39,600 --> 00:35:40,520
Come on, slow down.

736
00:35:53,120 --> 00:35:54,960
Look at your master since he got sick,

737
00:35:55,440 --> 00:35:56,680
he's aged several years.

738
00:35:57,120 --> 00:35:59,160
He can barely lift his feet when walking.

739
00:36:00,400 --> 00:36:01,200
He'll recover with some rest.

740
00:36:02,040 --> 00:36:03,880
Wasn't it a heart stent?

741
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:06,200
Why do the symptoms look like a stroke?

742
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:06,920
He's all muddled up.

743
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:08,080
Just shut your mouth.

744
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:09,600
That rotten mouth of yours,

745
00:36:09,600 --> 00:36:10,960
spouting nonsense day after day.

746
00:36:11,560 --> 00:36:12,560
Okay, okay, okay.

747
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:14,560
I'm just worried about him, aren't I?

748
00:36:14,720 --> 00:36:16,200
Say something nice, will you?

749
00:36:18,280 --> 00:36:19,040
Auntie Xin.

750
00:36:19,760 --> 00:36:21,400
I transferred you a thousand yuan.

751
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:23,320
Why did you transfer me money?

752
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:26,160
Because you're so nice to me.

753
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:28,120
Xiao Xing.

754
00:36:29,040 --> 00:36:31,080
Do you really love money?

755
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:32,040
Not really.

756
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:34,320
It's just that without money,

757
00:36:34,480 --> 00:36:36,000
you can't survive.

758
00:36:37,920 --> 00:36:39,520
You make a fair point.

759
00:36:40,720 --> 00:36:42,480
Then Auntie really wants to know,

760
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:44,920
what are you going to do with all that money?

761
00:36:44,920 --> 00:36:46,320
I want to fly far away,

762
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:48,280
and live the life I want.

763
00:36:55,560 --> 00:36:56,360
By the way, Xiao Xing,

764
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:58,400
do you want to know

765
00:36:58,400 --> 00:36:59,760
the secret to becoming

766
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:01,520
a super-rich tycoon?

767
00:37:01,520 --> 00:37:02,160
Yes.

768
00:37:03,440 --> 00:37:04,400
In Auntie's bag,

769
00:37:04,720 --> 00:37:06,760
there's a notebook made by Auntie's company.

770
00:37:09,160 --> 00:37:10,560
Now I'll give it to you.

771
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:11,880
Starting today,

772
00:37:11,880 --> 00:37:13,040
every single day,

773
00:37:13,040 --> 00:37:15,280
write one sentence in this notebook,

774
00:37:15,280 --> 00:37:16,600
something that made you happy.

775
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:19,560
Like, what tasty thing you ate today,

776
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:20,880
or maybe

777
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:23,280
a cute puppy you saw on the road.

778
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:24,480
Anything at all.

779
00:37:24,560 --> 00:37:27,120
It's just like saving money on your phone.

780
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:28,000
It's the same thing.

781
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:30,000
Don't underestimate it.

782
00:37:30,120 --> 00:37:31,720
Once you're done writing,

783
00:37:31,720 --> 00:37:32,880
you'll realize

784
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:34,400
that inside this notebook,

785
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:37,160
there's far more wealth than in your phone.

786
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:38,960
Thank you, Auntie.

787
00:37:39,320 --> 00:37:39,840
You're welcome.

788
00:37:42,040 --> 00:37:42,960
Auntie Xin,

789
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:45,320
I was in the wrong last time.

790
00:37:45,680 --> 00:37:47,960
I shouldn't have made that deal with my dad.

791
00:37:51,560 --> 00:37:52,160
Xiao Xing,

792
00:37:53,160 --> 00:37:54,280
you did nothing wrong.

793
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:01,840
It's us adults who failed.

794
00:38:06,200 --> 00:38:06,880
Yongnian.

795
00:38:08,840 --> 00:38:09,560
This time,

796
00:38:10,720 --> 00:38:11,640
after being discharged,

797
00:38:12,080 --> 00:38:13,120
how are you feeling?

798
00:38:16,960 --> 00:38:17,280
Here.

799
00:38:17,520 --> 00:38:18,160
Thank you.

800
00:38:21,600 --> 00:38:22,440
As for me,

801
00:38:22,680 --> 00:38:24,440
I've got to admit I'm getting old.

802
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:26,920
Since being discharged this time,

803
00:38:28,200 --> 00:38:30,720
I feel like I've gone downhill a lot.

804
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:33,680
That old drive I used to have

805
00:38:36,400 --> 00:38:37,760
seems to be gone.

806
00:38:38,800 --> 00:38:40,560
Maybe it's just my age.

807
00:38:41,480 --> 00:38:43,920
Each day I feel worse than the last.

808
00:38:46,520 --> 00:38:47,240
Yongnian,

809
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:50,920
don't talk to me about getting old.

810
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:53,200
I've taken your pulse.

811
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:55,960
Right now,

812
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:57,880
you've lost your sense of purpose.

813
00:38:58,680 --> 00:38:59,480
Before,

814
00:38:59,560 --> 00:39:00,840
you led Zhang Du

815
00:39:00,920 --> 00:39:02,200
in making Chengxin Tang paper

816
00:39:02,400 --> 00:39:03,400
and getting into Pine and Crane Studio.

817
00:39:03,880 --> 00:39:05,000
You still had

818
00:39:05,400 --> 00:39:07,600
the drive to restore your ancestors' glory.

819
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:10,120
But now,

820
00:39:10,440 --> 00:39:11,960
you've done everything you set out to do.

821
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:14,880
You just don't know what to do next.

822
00:39:15,800 --> 00:39:18,400
Your pulse reading is spot on.

823
00:39:23,720 --> 00:39:24,600
I've been thinking,

824
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:27,680
maybe I should just hand over the factory

825
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:30,160
and everything else

826
00:39:31,440 --> 00:39:33,480
to Xuan Yan as soon as possible.

827
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:36,840
The legacy our ancestors left us

828
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:39,600
should be put on his shoulders sooner.

829
00:39:40,120 --> 00:39:42,880
Sooner is better than later.

830
00:39:43,040 --> 00:39:44,880
Luckily, we're both still here

831
00:39:45,240 --> 00:39:47,840
to help him keep things in check.

832
00:39:49,280 --> 00:39:50,720
Xuan Yan, that boy,

833
00:39:50,720 --> 00:39:51,840
he's sensible and well-educated.

834
00:39:52,120 --> 00:39:53,560
Have a proper talk with him.

835
00:39:53,720 --> 00:39:54,640
It should work out.

836
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:56,840
If that really happens,

837
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:59,440
then I can spend the rest of my time

838
00:39:59,960 --> 00:40:02,080
focusing wholeheartedly

839
00:40:03,120 --> 00:40:05,440
on creating one truly great sheet of paper.

840
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:06,840
That way,

841
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:09,640
I can honor our ancestors.

842
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:11,040
That's a good idea.

843
00:40:11,040 --> 00:40:11,840
Sounds solid.

844
00:40:12,080 --> 00:40:13,320
Making one great sheet of paper,

845
00:40:13,480 --> 00:40:15,040
you'll have a purpose again.

846
00:40:17,440 --> 00:40:18,120
Right.

847
00:40:19,320 --> 00:40:21,920
Food's ready. Let's eat.

848
00:40:22,320 --> 00:40:22,920
Dig in.

849
00:40:23,840 --> 00:40:25,000
Try Auntie's cooking.

850
00:40:27,280 --> 00:40:27,680
Here.

851
00:40:28,160 --> 00:40:29,600
Try the chicken wings first.

852
00:40:29,720 --> 00:40:29,960
Thank you.

853
00:40:29,960 --> 00:40:31,520
This is my specialty dish.

854
00:40:33,040 --> 00:40:33,680
How is it?

855
00:40:34,160 --> 00:40:34,800
Delicious.

856
00:40:35,080 --> 00:40:37,080
Way better than Xiwang Restaurant.

857
00:40:38,640 --> 00:40:39,840
You sure know how to flatter.

858
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:41,000
Let Auntie peel a shrimp for you.

859
00:40:41,640 --> 00:40:42,600
How's it? Too salty?

860
00:40:43,200 --> 00:40:44,520
Not salty. It's tasty.

861
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:47,120
About me cooking for you,

862
00:40:47,120 --> 00:40:48,520
you can't tell your dad.

863
00:40:49,920 --> 00:40:51,320
It's a little secret between us.

864
00:40:51,320 --> 00:40:51,880
Okay?

865
00:40:51,880 --> 00:40:52,360
Okay.

866
00:40:52,640 --> 00:40:53,680
Four syllables.

867
00:40:53,680 --> 00:40:54,960
Sweetie, it's four syllables.

868
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:56,040
There's music.

869
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:57,040
Turn around.

870
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:58,120
Put on the headphones.

871
00:40:58,520 --> 00:40:59,600
Four syllables.

872
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:00,680
DJ spinning records.

873
00:41:01,800 --> 00:41:02,680
You got it!

874
00:41:02,680 --> 00:41:04,000
High five!

875
00:41:35,040 --> 00:41:38,280
You all prepared quite a nice spread today.

876
00:41:38,280 --> 00:41:39,320
All my favorites.

877
00:41:39,560 --> 00:41:40,880
Thanks for going to the trouble.

878
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:41,960
It's the least we could do, bro.

879
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:43,680
Fine wine and fine food.

880
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:46,480
And the flattery's laid on thick too.

881
00:41:47,520 --> 00:41:49,000
You've got something on your mind, huh?

882
00:41:50,080 --> 00:41:51,080
No, no, nothing at all.

883
00:41:53,720 --> 00:41:54,520
Nope.

884
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:57,040
If you ask me,

885
00:41:57,160 --> 00:41:58,160
whatever we need,

886
00:41:58,160 --> 00:41:59,480
just tell Brother Min straight up.

887
00:41:59,480 --> 00:42:00,640
Stop beating around the bush.

888
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:01,920
It's just us here.

889
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:03,120
Nothing to be shy about.

890
00:42:06,680 --> 00:42:08,160
Wanting to pull money out of someone's pocket

891
00:42:08,600 --> 00:42:10,680
without a good reason for it,

892
00:42:11,040 --> 00:42:12,800
anyone would feel awkward about that.

893
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:21,560
All right, don't be shy.

894
00:42:21,800 --> 00:42:22,440
Over the years,

895
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:24,280
haven't you taken enough from my pockets?

896
00:42:24,440 --> 00:42:25,480
See what I mean?

897
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:27,160
Look at that.

898
00:42:27,280 --> 00:42:28,920
Brother Min is Brother Min.

899
00:42:28,920 --> 00:42:30,960
Generous, always looking out for the brothers.

900
00:42:30,960 --> 00:42:32,800
Yeah, yes yes yes.

901
00:42:32,800 --> 00:42:34,480
Isn't looking out for my brothers a given?

902
00:42:35,840 --> 00:42:37,120
Take Erhu, for instance.

903
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:38,520
My family was poor when I was young,

904
00:42:38,600 --> 00:42:40,040
and I often ran over to his place to mooch meals.

905
00:42:41,160 --> 00:42:43,520
Sure, I'm the one who kicked him out of the association,

906
00:42:44,080 --> 00:42:45,720
but I can't really just abandon him, right?

907
00:42:45,720 --> 00:42:46,240
Right, right, right.

908
00:42:46,240 --> 00:42:47,800
You've still gotta help your own when they need it.

909
00:42:48,040 --> 00:42:48,880
I can't just

910
00:42:48,960 --> 00:42:50,600
watch him starve.

911
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:51,120
Right, right, right.

912
00:42:53,360 --> 00:42:54,800
But if I look out for my brothers,

913
00:42:56,040 --> 00:42:58,160
shouldn't the brothers show me a little consideration too?
